quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  4,95,"Those believers who sit (at home) without receiving any injury are not equal to those who strive in the way of God with their wealth and their persons. God has been more gracious to those who strive with their wealth and their persons by (giving them a higher) rank over those who sit (at home), and to each God has promised good but God has been more gracious to those who strive, by giving them a greater reward compared to those who sit (at home)"
  4,96,"ranks from Him and protective forgiveness and mercy and God is Protectively Forgiving, Merciful"
  4,97,"Certainly, (when) the angels will cause to die those who were unjust to themselves, they will ask, \"In what (state) were you?\" They will reply, \"We were weak in the earth.\" (The angels) will say, \"Was not the earth of God spacious so that you could have migrated therein?\" Then their settling place will be hell and it will be an evil destination"
  4,98,except the weak among the men and the women and the children who neither have (any) means in their power nor (anyone) to guide them to the way (for migration)
  4,99,"So those, it may be that God will pardon them and God is Pardoning, Protectively Forgiving"
  4,100,"And whoever migrates in the way of God, he will find numerous places of refuge in the earth and abundance (in livelihood). And whoever goes forth from his house as a migrant to God and His messenger then death catches him, his reward has then become incumbent on God and God is Protectively Forgiving, Merciful"
  4,101,"When you travel through the land, it is permissible for you to shorten the prayer—˹especially˺ if you fear an attack by the disbelievers. Indeed, the disbelievers are your sworn enemies"